Qatar International Petroleum
Marketing Co., or Tasweeq, offered to sell deodorized field
condensate and low-sulfur condensate for loading in December,
according to a notice e-mailed from the state-owned company.  Details of the offer are as follows:  Condensate is a type of light crude oil produced in
association with natural gas and is usually processed into fuel
products such as diesel and naphtha, a raw material for gasoline
and chemicals.  To contact the reporter on this story:
